                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="19251" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Tue, 29 Aug 2006 05:17:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;What exact exception do you get there - the nested exception of the HibernateSystemException? I assume it&apos;s a PropertyValueException?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This means that you haven&apos;t even hit the database. Rather, Hibernate &lt;b&gt;itself&lt;/b&gt; found that you violated the non-null constraint in your object model.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Hence, I have added default translation of PropertyValueException to DataIntegrityViolationException... to catch that case as well.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Juergen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="19268" author="cblin" created="Tue, 29 Aug 2006 18:18:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes this was effectively a PropertyValueException thrown by Hibernate before hitting the database.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the quick fix.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;chris&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="19534" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Mon, 11 Sep 2006 08:01:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;OK, good to hear that it works for you now &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Juergen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
